This sample will take a BED, GTF or GFF file and will create a file for each chromosome in the input and will split the elements accordingly.

Note: The sample must be launched in the same directory as the data file.

The sample signature is:
splitToChrom <fileToSplit> <fileType> <outputPrefix>

Example of usage with the joined sample file:
./splitToChrom sample.bed BED test.bed
